(1706, '0.00', '[{"id": 10402, "name": "Music"}, {"id": 35, "name": "Comedy"}, {"id": 18, "name": "Drama"}]', 'http://www.takingwoodstockthemovie.co.uk/', 'en', 'The story of Elliot Tiber and his family, who inadvertently played a pivotal role in making the famed Woodstock Music and Arts Festival into the happening that it was. When Elliot hears that a neighboring town has pulled the permit on a hippie music festival, he calls the producers thinking he could drum up some much-needed business for his parents'' run-down motel. Three weeks later, half a million people are on their way to his neighbor’s farm in White Lake, New York, and Elliot finds himself swept up in a generation-defining experience that would change his life–and American culture–forever.', '[{"name": "Focus Features", "id": 10146}]', '2009-09-03', '0.00', '120.00', 'A Generation Began In His Backyard.', 'Taking Woodstock', '6.2', 127, 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzE5NDYzM2YtMjlhMS00Yjc5LWFhZWUtNjQ4ODVhZTQ4OTFkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDk3NzU2MTQ@._V1_QL75_UX190_CR0,6,190,281_.jpg'),
(1707, '28000000.00', '[{"id": 18, "name": "Drama"}, {"id": 36, "name": "History"}]', 'NA', 'en', 'In 1980, the United States Ice Hockey team''s coach, Herb Brooks, put a ragtag squad of college kids up against the legendary juggernaut from the Soviet Union at the Olympic Games. Despite the long odds, Team USA carried the pride of a nation yearning for a distraction from world events. With the world watching, the team rose to the occasion, prompting broadcaster Al Michaels'' now famous question to the millions viewing at home: "Do you believe in miracles?" Yes!', '[{"name": "Walt Disney", "id": 5888}]', '2004-02-06', '64445708.00', '135.00', 'If you believe in yourself, anything can happen.', 'Miracle', '7.0', 159, 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjEyOTk1OTcyNV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTYwNjMzNDU3._V1_QL75_UX190_CR0,0,190,281_.jpg'),
